article.headline: UNLV 92, SE Louisiana 56
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Anthony Marshall scored 14 points to lead UNLV to a 92-56 victory over Southeastern Louisiana on Wednesday night. Five Rebels reached double digits in scoring, as Brice Massamba added 12 points and four assists, Justin Hawkins had 11 points and four assists, Chace Stanback scored 10 points and Karam Mashour, who was making his UNLV debut, scored 10 points, all in the second half. UNLV (2-0), which connected on 63 percent (35-for-56) of its field-goal attempts, had 11 players score at least two points. The Lions (1-1) were led by Trent Hutchin with 18 points and Brandon Fortenberry with 16.
